Bottom line is - you do not need hadoop until you cross 2TB of data to be processed (uncompressed).
Modern servers ( bare metal ones, not what AWS sells you ) are REALLY FAST and can crunch massive amounts of data.<p>Just use a proper tools, well optimized code written in C/C++/Go/etc - not all the crappy JAVA framework-in-a-framework^N architecture that abstracts thinking about the CPU speed.<p>Bottom line, the popular saying is true:
&quot;Hadoop is about writing crappy code and then running it on a massive scale.&quot;
